  "text": "One useful application of the Lanczos algorithm is (kernel) PCA. As shown in [CITATION_1] , the eigenspace projection of a given vector can be computed directly from the eigenvectors of the truncated tridiagonalized matrix T r . The computational cost to diagonalize T r is only O(r) when r ≪ ℓ. A similar idea is used in [CITATION_2] to accelerate a Markov decision process.",
